                that Heraclitus thinks we can't do? Obviously I
                <em>can</em>do a little in-and-out-and-back-in-again shuffle with my foot at a riverbank. But is it
                <em>the same</em>river from moment to moment â€“ the water flowing over my foot spills toward the ocean while new waters join the river at its source â€“ and am I the same person?</p>



